#Requiremnts for Shape analysis
xtc2shp  #for input generation
config.yaml
avg_plotting.py #for plotting and averages 

#to run


bash run_shape.sh ../../../../../../../../../simulations/zinc_bound/6JWH_129-151/exp/replicate1/charmm36m/NH2_CT2_terminals/md/Mol_An/update.gro  ../../../../../../../../../simulations/zinc_bound/6JWH_129-151/exp/replicate1/charmm36m/NH2_CT2_terminals/md/Mol_An/center_traj.xtc 

#It will use the gro and xtc to build an MDanalysis universe and extract the coordinates and a reference structure of the atom ligands and the centre of coordination specified in the geometries.ini file.
#The 'zn' simply indicates the centre of the coordination, in our case a Zinc ion.

NOTES

#In cases for which the coordination changes i.e 3 atoms coordinating a metal instead of 4g, the user will need to manually modify run_shape.sh
accordingly in the generation of the dat file and plotting (For more on input file of Shape software loook : http://www.ee.ub.edu/index.php?option=com_jdownloads&Itemid=529&view=viewcategory&catid=3 ):



Example :
----------------

$ tetrahedral Zn 		   
! keyword, name of coords. file    
%external traj.shp		   
%reference ref_geometries.ref      
%fullout                           
3 1				   
1 2 3 4 0 			   

##### for plotting 


python plot.py -i r1_6jwh_129-151_charmm22star.tab -p -b -c Trigonal planar Pyramid fac-Trivacant octahedron mer-Trivacant octahedron Coord-PDB -t "title" -o "out_name"

